5000|$|The {{exhibition}} {{is described as}} the [...] "first ever museum exhibition of airport architecture," [...] and offers visitors a tour through the past, present, and future of air travel while focusing especially on six of Fentress Architects' most notable <b>airport</b> <b>designs</b> and their role in defining the modern airport. The exhibition also includes a segment called Airport of the Future that showcases work from a student exhibition as well as theoretical <b>airport</b> <b>designs</b> in the years 2062 and 2162. [...] These theoretical airports, developed by an internal think tank at Fentress Architects consisting of architects, engineers from Stanford University, futurists, and artists, became a popular highlight of the show, and will be exhibited separately {{from the rest of}} the exhibition at the A+D Museum in Los Angeles beginning in March 2013.|$|R
